00:15:01.346 --> 00:15:04.023
I just authorized an
excavation of the back patio.

246
00:15:04.078 --> 00:15:06.241
I think there's
something buried there.

247
00:15:06.308 --> 00:15:08.242
What are we doing
to find Neil Perry?

248
00:15:08.268 --> 00:15:11.023
I put his name in the automated
system and notified the FBI.

249
00:15:11.059 --> 00:15:12.174
Airports on alert?

250
00:15:12.207 --> 00:15:14.551
Airports. train stations.
bus lines.

251
00:15:14.609 --> 00:15:16.214
We should track
his credit cards.

252
00:15:16.246 --> 00:15:17.203
Already done.

253
00:15:17.249 --> 00:15:18.922
along with A.T.M.s
and bank accounts.

254
00:15:19.007 --> 00:15:20.823
I also put a tap
on his home phone.

255
00:15:23.627 --> 00:15:26.682
- Seems you thought of everything.
- It seems that way.

256
00:15:33.937 --> 00:15:36.593
- Look. Maria --
- No need to apologize.

257
00:15:36.639 --> 00:15:39.002
I don't require your
approval to do my job.

258
00:15:39.057 --> 00:15:40.033
I  know that.

259
00:15:40.057 --> 00:15:42.753
I've been kicking your ass 'cause
I knew you had this in you.

260
00:15:42.816 --> 00:15:44.122
Well. thank you

261
00:15:44.167 --> 00:15:46.361
for making me the
woman I am today.

262
00:15:47.738 --> 00:15:49.594
I love you to everything.

263
00:15:52.108 --> 00:15:54.361
I love you to everything. too.

264
00:16:00.419 --> 00:16:02.842
He's not gonna
hit you anymore.

265
00:16:03.357 --> 00:16:05.334
He told me at the carnival.

266
00:16:05.419 --> 00:16:07.292
I made him promise.

267
00:16:10.389 --> 00:16:12.672
Thank you. baby.

268
00:16:19.299 --> 00:16:22.493
I haven't had time to
process as much as the kids.

269
00:16:22.638 --> 00:16:25.493
And Paul was supposed to be
locked up for another year.

270
00:16:26.188 --> 00:16:29.053
Cody seems to be
processing okay.

271
00:16:29.608 --> 00:16:31.392
Cody's too young.

272
00:16:31.578 --> 00:16:34.441
A dad's just a concept to him.
not a person.

273
00:16:34.769 --> 00:16:36.311
But Astor --

274
00:16:36.868 --> 00:16:39.551
She remembers what
he put us through.

275
00:16:42.588 --> 00:16:44.683
Well. at least you're
not married anymore.

276
00:16:46.278 --> 00:16:48.004
That's just it.

277
00:16:48.288 --> 00:16:50.394
Technically. we are.

278
00:16:51.079 --> 00:16:52.604
When Paul went to prison.

279
00:16:52.628 --> 00:16:54.021
I started divorce proceedings.

280
00:16:54.086 --> 00:16:56.481
but he refused to
sign the paperwork.

281
00:16:56.717 --> 00:16:58.832
As a power play?

282
00:16:59.096 --> 00:17:00.863
I don't think so.

283
00:17:00.906 --> 00:17:03.471
I think for all the
darkness that haunts him.

284
00:17:03.506 --> 00:17:05.623
Paul loves having a family.

285
00:17:06.516 --> 00:17:09.004
I think he's just
afraid to let go.

286
00:17:10.537 --> 00:17:13.202
When did you first notice it?

287
00:17:13.778 --> 00:17:18.384
This darkness inside
the guy you fell for.

288
00:17:19.108 --> 00:17:21.153
I always knew it was there.

289
00:17:21.208 --> 00:17:24.552
I guess I just didn't
think I deserved better...

290
00:17:25.257 --> 00:17:27.291
Till I met you.

291
00:17:35.998 --> 00:17:38.673
I have a dark side. too.

292
00:17:40.938 --> 00:17:43.002
What?
I do.

293
00:17:43.238 --> 00:17:45.274
Somehow I doubt that.

294
00:17:45.748 --> 00:17:47.944
You have a good heart. Dexter.

295
00:17:48.088 --> 00:17:51.332
You're not like Paul.
You don't hurt people.

296
00:17:56.419 --> 00:17:58.192
Innocent people.

297
00:18:03.596 --> 00:18:06.101
I don't hurt innocent people.

298
00:18:29.659 --> 00:18:32.622
Hey. dude. the bowling alley's
around the corner.

299
00:18:36.447 --> 00:18:39.024
Hey. I'm looking
for Jeremy Downs.

300
00:18:39.107 --> 00:18:40.103
Jeremy?

301
00:18:40.188 --> 00:18:42.953
He vacated the premises.

302
00:18:44.047 --> 00:18:45.742
Focus.

303
00:18:46.047 --> 00:18:47.893
I'm trying to find Jeremy.

304
00:18:48.428 --> 00:18:50.102
Oh. I get it.

305
00:18:53.209 --> 00:18:54.792
Look. man.

306
00:18:54.979 --> 00:18:57.182
I'm not really into
that homo shit.

307
00:18:57.329 --> 00:19:00.144
but I'm kind of short
on money for weed.

308
00:19:00.288 --> 00:19:03.532
so I guess I'll do it for
less than Jeremy's charging.

309
00:19:03.768 --> 00:19:05.622
Wait. What does
Jeremy charge?

310
00:19:05.669 --> 00:19:07.522
Jeremy's selling himself?

311
00:19:07.716 --> 00:19:11.661
I mean. he's always hanging out with the
Brokeback boys down at Flamingo Park.

312
00:19:11.827 --> 00:19:14.604
Comes back with
fistfuls of cash.

313
00:19:21.167 --> 00:19:25.162
It's me. Get your ass over
to Neil Perry's place.

314
00:19:25.288 --> 00:19:27.884
- You're gonna want to see this.
- Deb. it's my day off.

315
00:19:27.918 --> 00:19:29.653
Just get your ass over here.

316
00:19:29.838 --> 00:19:32.782
We're about to bust open the
goods on the ice-truck killer.

317
00:19:45.587 --> 00:19:47.513
Not what I expected.

318
00:20:23.126 --> 00:20:24.574
So lifelike.

319
00:20:36.757 --> 00:20:38.123
Hey. Dex.

320
00:20:38.306 --> 00:20:39.964
I thought you'd
want to be here.

321
00:20:40.059 --> 00:20:42.503
Something's buried down there.
Masuka's been digging all night.

322
00:20:42.526 --> 00:20:43.982
I hate to break
this to you. Deb.

323
00:20:44.006 --> 00:20:46.004
but you know you've got
the wrong guy here. right?

324
00:20:46.679 --> 00:20:49.363
The ice-truck killer drains
the blood from his victims.

325
00:20:49.398 --> 00:20:51.942
freezes their bodies. and
only then severs their limbs.

326
00:20:51.979 --> 00:20:54.462
It's clean and efficient --
His psychological signature.

327
00:20:54.697 --> 00:20:57.423
Neil Perry. on the other hand.
stuffs roadkill.

328
00:20:57.468 --> 00:20:59.413
Yeah. and turns it into
fucked-up fantasy shit.

329
00:20:59.446 --> 00:21:00.902
But the fantasies
are all wrong!

330
00:21:00.956 --> 00:21:02.554
The guy we're looking for
wouldn't turn

331
00:21:02.588 --> 00:21:04.481
dead. dirty things
into living cartoons.

332
00:21:04.599 --> 00:21:06.791
- He'd find that pathetic.
- How do you know?

333
00:21:07.446 --> 00:21:09.133
Because it is pathetic.

334
00:21:09.696 --> 00:21:11.224
Deb. trust me.

335
00:21:11.308 --> 00:21:14.401
Neil Perry is not a killer.
He's a dabbler. He's a waste of time.

336
00:21:14.436 --> 00:21:17.402
If the guy we're looking for took
his early fantasies out on animals.

337
00:21:17.429 --> 00:21:19.051
he'd bury them.
not display them.

338
00:21:19.089 --> 00:21:22.212
And what about an early human kill?
Would he bury that. too?

339
00:21:22.529 --> 00:21:24.832
- Sure. Probably.
- Then turn around.

340
00:21:25.558 --> 00:21:27.133
You were saying?

341
00:21:28.729 --> 00:21:30.834
It looks like an adult female.

342
00:21:31.607 --> 00:21:33.951
Any idea how long the
body's been down there?

343
00:21:34.137 --> 00:21:35.591
Based on decomposition.

344
00:21:35.776 --> 00:21:38.073
she's been tits up for two.
maybe three years.

345
00:21:38.217 --> 00:21:39.912
We'll know more
after the autopsy.

346
00:21:39.948 --> 00:21:42.271
What happened to the limbs?
Did they rot off?

347
00:21:42.826 --> 00:21:45.881
No. They're clean cuts.

348
00:21:46.028 --> 00:21:47.994
But he didn't chop
up the whole body.

349
00:21:48.456 --> 00:21:50.371
This could be
Perry's first kill.

350
00:21:50.607 --> 00:21:52.583
like he was experimenting.

351
00:21:53.087 --> 00:21:55.533
You're the expert. Dex.
What do you think?

352
00:21:57.336 --> 00:21:59.723
Sure.
Sounds good.

353
00:21:59.859 --> 00:22:01.972
<i>Actually. it sounds
perfectly awful.</i>

354
00:22:03.089 --> 00:22:06.802
<i>For weeks. I've felt like a
student in a master class.</i>

355
00:22:06.946 --> 00:22:09.573
<i>Is it really possible that
the master's on the run?</i>

356
00:22:11.059 --> 00:22:12.412
<i>And even more tragic.</i>

357
00:22:12.558 --> 00:22:14.624
<i>does  he live in a double-wide?</i>

358
00:22:16.458 --> 00:22:18.892
The gravitron goes so fast. mom.

359
00:22:19.037 --> 00:22:21.624
My dad took me on
it three times.

360
00:22:21.857 --> 00:22:23.373
Wow.
Is that so?

361
00:22:25.367 --> 00:22:27.994
All right. let me cut you
guys up some fruit.

362
00:22:28.209 --> 00:22:30.763
Astor wouldn't go.
She was afraid.

363
00:22:30.959 --> 00:22:33.813
So what?
I don't like fast rides.

364
00:22:38.679 --> 00:22:40.264
Hello?

365
00:22:42.449 --> 00:22:45.343
- Who wants doughnuts?
- I do.

366
00:22:45.377 --> 00:22:47.303
Paul. you can't just walk
in here whenever you want.

367
00:22:47.359 --> 00:22:48.804
You don't live here anymore.

368
00:22:49.868 --> 00:22:52.681
Sorry about that.
Old habits.

369
00:22:52.829 --> 00:22:54.933
I'll ring the
doorbell next time.

370
00:22:58.869 --> 00:23:01.863
I got these for you.

371
00:23:03.907 --> 00:23:08.653
All right. I'll just put them
in... something.

372
00:23:08.849 --> 00:23:10.574
Dad. can I have
a doughnut?

373
00:23:10.718 --> 00:23:12.354
You got it. buddy.
Coming up.

374
00:23:12.409 --> 00:23:14.422
What. now you're making
me out to be the bad guy?

375
00:23:14.519 --> 00:23:16.201
They haven't had breakfast yet!

376
00:23:17.668 --> 00:23:20.912
You know what? Kidlet. my bad.
Sorry about that.

377
00:23:21.096 --> 00:23:22.942
These doughnuts are
for after school.

378
00:23:22.989 --> 00:23:25.762
But tell what? I could whip up
some eggs and pancakes.

379
00:23:25.809 --> 00:23:28.614
- Paul!
- Very little syrup. I promise.

380
00:23:28.656 --> 00:23:30.913
And meat.
You into meat?

381
00:23:31.017 --> 00:23:32.343
I like meat.

382
00:23:32.376 --> 00:23:36.532
I like meat on my feet.
It's real squishy.

383
00:23:36.556 --> 00:23:37.481
Paul.

384
00:23:38.986 --> 00:23:40.901
You can't do this
anymore. Paul.

385
00:23:40.956 --> 00:23:42.884
What?! What?!

386
00:23:43.108 --> 00:23:44.771
Help raise my kids?!

387
00:23:45.178 --> 00:23:47.993
Yes. I can. That's my job.

388
00:23:50.368 --> 00:23:52.191
All right. look.

389
00:23:53.566 --> 00:23:55.811
I can't even
begin to understand

390
00:23:55.859 --> 00:23:58.091
how difficult this
has been for you. Rita.

391
00:23:58.119 --> 00:24:00.152
being a single mom. okay?

392
00:24:01.638 --> 00:24:03.242
And for that. I...

393
00:24:03.657 --> 00:24:05.364
I'm eternally sorry.

394
00:24:06.917 --> 00:24:08.641
I let you down.

395
00:24:10.057 --> 00:24:11.944
I let everybody down.

396
00:24:16.558 --> 00:24:19.894
But if I could just
find that frying pan.

397
00:24:20.079 --> 00:24:23.653
Astor... Want to help
me find the frying pan?

398
00:24:31.486 --> 00:24:33.781
We got a profile of Neil Perry.

399
00:24:33.927 --> 00:24:35.424
He's a computer expert.

400
00:24:35.519 --> 00:24:36.993
I.Q. off the chart.

401
00:24:37.028 --> 00:24:38.703
He's a loner.
no pryors.

402
00:24:38.757 --> 00:24:40.504
His father split when he was 6.

403
00:24:40.536 --> 00:24:42.604
His mother was an
alcoholic. abusive.

404
00:24:42.679 --> 00:24:44.823
and possibly
his first victim.

405
00:24:45.517 --> 00:24:47.051
Roberta Perry.

406
00:24:47.289 --> 00:24:49.992
Dental records say she was
the one under the patio.

407
00:24:50.039 --> 00:24:51.652
Now. Neil kept her death quiet

408
00:24:51.688 --> 00:24:53.371
by cashing her
social-security checks

409
00:24:53.409 --> 00:24:54.972
for the last two years but.

410
00:24:55.009 --> 00:24:56.782
he did not kill her
for the money.

411
00:24:56.809 --> 00:24:58.493
Morgan?

412
00:24:58.768 --> 00:25:00.501
We think he wanted release.

413
00:25:00.636 --> 00:25:02.612
Roberta Perry ran
her son's life.

414
00:25:02.799 --> 00:25:04.572
controlled him.
beat him as a kid.

415
00:25:04.718 --> 00:25:06.653
We think he dreamt about
killing her for years.

416
00:25:06.689 --> 00:25:08.571
I just spoke with Perry's
cellphone provider.

417
00:25:08.609 --> 00:25:10.012
Can they track his location?

418
00:25:10.049 --> 00:25:11.853
No signal --
He probably turned off his phone.

419
00:25:11.896 --> 00:25:14.203
But. according to records.
he used it

420
00:25:14.249 --> 00:25:15.313
on some of the nights

421
00:25:15.338 --> 00:25:17.083
the ice-truck killer
victims were taken.

422
00:25:17.117 --> 00:25:17.903
Who did he call?

423
00:25:18.027 --> 00:25:19.863
Voice mail. mostly.
checking messages.

424
00:25:19.908 --> 00:25:21.994
Verizon triangulated
the location.

425
00:25:22.168 --> 00:25:23.912
All the calls came
from the same place --

426
00:25:23.946 --> 00:25:26.382
a six-block area on
southwest 8th street.

427
00:25:26.426 --> 00:25:27.523
The Tamiami Trail.

428
00:25:27.567 --> 00:25:29.493
That strip's full
of No-Tell motels.

429
00:25:29.528 --> 00:25:31.282
It's like a happy hunting
ground for hookers.

430
00:25:31.317 --> 00:25:34.313
There's a good chance that's
where he's killing his victims.

431
00:25:34.319 --> 00:25:36.092
Let's recanvass
the area for leads.

432
00:25:36.139 --> 00:25:38.023
Now that we've got
a photo of this guy.

433
00:25:38.057 --> 00:25:40.412
maybe we can find somebody
who actually saw him.

434
00:25:40.548 --> 00:25:42.002
Let's go.

435
00:25:43.196 --> 00:25:45.163
You're starting
to look like her.

436
00:25:45.717 --> 00:25:48.033
Want to stop by your house.
check in with your family?

437
00:25:48.068 --> 00:25:49.613
I'd rather check in
with your brother.

438
00:25:49.646 --> 00:25:51.801
His instincts are usually
pretty good on this stuff.

439
00:25:51.846 --> 00:25:54.082
Yeah. not today.
He'd just piss on our parade.

440
00:25:54.106 --> 00:25:55.723
He needs his day off.

441
00:25:57.317 --> 00:25:59.061
<i>The first time I saw his work.</i>

442
00:25:59.096 --> 00:26:01.013
<i>I felt like a Spanish explorer</i>

443
00:26:01.048 --> 00:26:03.423
<i>landing of the shores
of the New World.</i>

444
00:26:03.736 --> 00:26:05.851
<i>No blood in the victims.</i>

445
00:26:05.916 --> 00:26:07.993
<i>no spatter.
no stain.</i>

446
00:26:09.368 --> 00:26:11.383
<i>Deb is wrong about him.</i>

447
00:26:11.986 --> 00:26:14.803
<i>It's okay.
Hell. I've made mistakes.</i>

448
00:26:15.087 --> 00:26:18.374
<i>In fact. I'm about to
correct a big one right now.</i>

449
00:26:20.156 --> 00:26:21.944
<i>Jeremy Downs.</i>

450
00:26:24.349 --> 00:26:25.981
Hey. you want company?

451
00:26:26.216 --> 00:26:28.324
Just keep walking
and looking ahead.

452
00:26:29.747 --> 00:26:32.404
Some mangroves over by
the lake. we can go in there.

453
00:26:32.436 --> 00:26:33.923
It's too public.

454
00:26:34.039 --> 00:26:35.412
My car's in the parking lot.

455
00:26:35.886 --> 00:26:38.985
- Are your windows tinted?
- I said. "eyes front."

456
00:26:41.997 --> 00:26:43.533
What's wrong?

457
00:26:48.439 --> 00:26:50.124
Shit. Shit!

458
00:26:50.779 --> 00:26:52.552
Get the fuck out of my way!

459
00:26:53.528 --> 00:26:56.014
Take it easy. Jeremy!
Stay right there!

460
00:26:56.197 --> 00:26:58.642
Take him down!
Take him down!

461
00:27:00.168 --> 00:27:03.362
Hands behind your back.
Stand up! Stand up!

462
00:27:16.707 --> 00:27:18.914
Miami Metro P.D.
Can we have a minute?

463
00:27:18.988 --> 00:27:20.003
Yeah.

464
00:27:20.090 --> 00:27:22.813
- This guy look familiar?
- I don't know.

465
00:27:23.089 --> 00:27:24.443
They come.
They go.

466
00:27:24.727 --> 00:27:27.264
You get it?
They "come."

467
00:27:27.349 --> 00:27:30.254
Look. my feet are aching
from pounding the pavement.

468
00:27:30.287 --> 00:27:31.855
You think you
could help us out?

469
00:27:31.910 --> 00:27:33.523
What's your name?

470
00:27:33.809 --> 00:27:36.623
Laline Consuelo Garciá Gómez.

471
00:27:39.927 --> 00:27:41.593
Laline...

472
00:27:42.048 --> 00:27:44.763
Oíste del hombre que le
dicen el ice-truck killer?

473
00:27:44.807 --> 00:27:46.152
Sí.

474
00:27:46.188 --> 00:27:47.552
Puede ser el.

475
00:27:47.598 --> 00:27:49.613
So let's try this again.

476
00:27:49.847 --> 00:27:52.043
Have you seen this man?

477
00:27:53.857 --> 00:27:55.355
He's a regular.

478
00:27:55.390 --> 00:27:57.205
Rents a room by
the month -- Cash.

479
00:27:57.248 --> 00:27:58.522
When was the last
time he was here?

480
00:27:58.550 --> 00:28:01.214
He's here now. He brought a
girl to his room this morning.

481
00:28:01.257 --> 00:28:02.663
A working girl?
A hooker?

482
00:28:02.689 --> 00:28:04.902
- All his guests are hoo...
- What's the room number?

483
00:28:04.957 --> 00:28:06.553
20.
Here's the master.

484
00:28:06.587 --> 00:28:08.912
Call for backup.
Let's hope this girl is still alive.

485
00:28:10.009 --> 00:28:11.454
Do we wait for tactical?

486
00:28:11.508 --> 00:28:13.422
Not with a possible
victim in there.

487
00:28:28.968 --> 00:28:29.854
Clear.

488
00:28:30.548 --> 00:28:33.314
It's okay. We're here now.
You're safe.

489
00:28:36.368 --> 00:28:40.032
Please get me out -- Hurry --
Before he comes back!

490
00:28:40.229 --> 00:28:42.165
- Where is he?
- Please. I want to get out!

491
00:28:42.199 --> 00:28:43.454
Where was he going?

492
00:28:43.730 --> 00:28:46.074
The liquor store.
He said he's coming right back.

493
00:28:49.590 --> 00:28:50.704
What?

494
00:28:54.997 --> 00:28:56.974
Hey. where's Doakes?
He paged me.

495
00:28:57.018 --> 00:28:58.903
We need your report from
that kid in the alley.

496
00:28:58.940 --> 00:29:00.105
But it's my day off!

