is down to one.</i>

752
00:42:46.087 --> 00:42:47.575
How --

753
00:42:47.927 --> 00:42:49.665
What are you doing here?
Are you a cop?

754
00:42:49.860 --> 00:42:51.752
The cameras are off.
I have one minute.

755
00:42:52.087 --> 00:42:54.335
Tell me why.
I need to know.

756
00:42:54.407 --> 00:42:56.152
- Why what?
- Don't!

757
00:42:58.647 --> 00:43:00.323
You killed again.

758
00:43:00.409 --> 00:43:01.862
I told you --
I warned you --

759
00:43:01.907 --> 00:43:05.323
Don't kill anyone who
doesn't deserve to die.

760
00:43:05.408 --> 00:43:07.195
Why did you do it?

761
00:43:10.427 --> 00:43:12.834
To feel something different.

762
00:43:14.769 --> 00:43:16.853
Different than what?

763
00:43:18.360 --> 00:43:21.173
What do you normally feel?

764
00:43:28.940 --> 00:43:30.455
Nothing.

765
00:43:30.518 --> 00:43:32.184
Fucking nothing at all!

766
00:43:32.229 --> 00:43:34.866
I hate every fucking
goddamn second of it.

767
00:43:34.910 --> 00:43:36.485
I can't stand it --

768
00:43:36.558 --> 00:43:38.184
Living my life in my head.

769
00:43:53.539 --> 00:43:55.624
Does killing make it better?

770
00:43:58.110 --> 00:43:59.284
No.

771
00:44:00.480 --> 00:44:01.865
Worse.

772
00:44:02.599 --> 00:44:05.133
Fucking worse than ever.

773
00:44:07.210 --> 00:44:09.233
Put your hands on the table.

774
00:44:11.241 --> 00:44:12.354
Do it.

775
00:44:18.508 --> 00:44:20.476
I'm a lot like you. you know?

776
00:44:20.521 --> 00:44:22.113
Yeah. right.

777
00:44:22.159 --> 00:44:23.685
You're a killer?

778
00:44:27.540 --> 00:44:29.465
I'm empty...

779
00:44:33.070 --> 00:44:37.583
...but I found a way to make
it feel less bottomless.

780
00:44:41.750 --> 00:44:44.653
- How?
- Pretend.

781
00:44:45.170 --> 00:44:48.414
You pretend the feelings
are there for the world.

782
00:44:48.510 --> 00:44:50.285
for the people around you.

783
00:44:52.959 --> 00:44:55.485
Who knows?
Maybe one day they will be.

784
00:44:56.000 --> 00:44:57.646
What the hell are
you doing. Morgan?

785
00:44:57.689 --> 00:44:59.675
I'm scraping under the nails
for blood. Almost done.

786
00:44:59.718 --> 00:45:00.813
Get out.

787
00:45:00.878 --> 00:45:02.474
I want 10 more minutes
with this piece of shit

788
00:45:02.530 --> 00:45:04.283
before his lawyer shows.

789
00:45:07.621 --> 00:45:08.646
Stand up!

790
00:45:10.388 --> 00:45:12.493
<i>Living my life in my head --</i>

791
00:45:12.691 --> 00:45:14.795
<i>I know exactly
what Jeremy means.</i>

792
00:45:14.980 --> 00:45:17.324
<i>At least I had
someone to talk to --</i>

793
00:45:17.459 --> 00:45:19.706
<i>Harry. my foster father.</i>

794
00:45:19.798 --> 00:45:22.013
<i>He spent endless hours
teaching me</i>

795
00:45:22.118 --> 00:45:23.504
<i>how to survive.</i>

796
00:45:23.561 --> 00:45:25.714
Excuse me. Are you
Jeremy Downs' lawyer?

797
00:45:25.758 --> 00:45:27.704
Yes. I am. I'm just heading
over to see him.

798
00:45:27.759 --> 00:45:29.275
Sooner would be better.

799
00:45:30.739 --> 00:45:33.323
- Seriously.
- Thank you.

800
00:45:40.990 --> 00:45:44.515
My mom died when I was 16 --
Cancer --

801
00:45:44.838 --> 00:45:48.506
And then it was just me.
my brother. my dad.

802
00:45:48.738 --> 00:45:51.693
- You have a brother?
- Yeah. Dexter.

803
00:45:51.931 --> 00:45:54.163
He and my dad were...
really tight.

804
00:45:54.199 --> 00:45:55.973
You know. they were always
spending time together.

805
00:45:56.210 --> 00:45:58.454
I guess I was jealous.

806
00:45:59.141 --> 00:46:01.483
What. you mean you weren't
daddy's little girl?

807
00:46:01.720 --> 00:46:04.074
No. I was...
kind of.

808
00:46:04.108 --> 00:46:07.155
He just took a special interest
in Dex. you know?

809
00:46:07.299 --> 00:46:09.995
I think that's why I became a cop.
That's what he was.

810
00:46:10.420 --> 00:46:13.366
I thought maybe he would give
me more attention or something.

811
00:46:13.398 --> 00:46:14.754
And did he?

812
00:46:15.099 --> 00:46:16.794
Not really...

813
00:46:17.569 --> 00:46:19.555
But we had our moments.

814
00:46:20.968 --> 00:46:23.883
What about you?
How'd you become...

815
00:46:24.899 --> 00:46:26.536
Captain hook?

816
00:46:27.739 --> 00:46:29.373
Well. when I was little.

817
00:46:29.428 --> 00:46:31.625
my mom got in
a car accident.

818
00:46:31.680 --> 00:46:33.493
She lost both her legs.

819
00:46:34.689 --> 00:46:35.854
It's terrible.

820
00:46:37.010 --> 00:46:39.074
I remember when it happened.

821
00:46:39.350 --> 00:46:41.656
I just wanted to put
her back together...

822
00:46:42.119 --> 00:46:44.605
You know. like Humpty-Dumpty.

823
00:46:45.108 --> 00:46:48.494
Just the pieces weren't... around.

824
00:47:14.870 --> 00:47:17.196
<i>I'm going to miss my playmate.</i>

825
00:47:21.051 --> 00:47:22.885
<i>Sure. there's
Rita and the kids.</i>

826
00:47:22.939 --> 00:47:25.196
<i>but they don't
know the real me.</i>

827
00:47:25.829 --> 00:47:28.275
<i>They can never
know the real me.</i>

828
00:47:30.031 --> 00:47:32.405
<i>And now the father is back.</i>

829
00:47:34.668 --> 00:47:36.553
<i>Things have changed.</i>

830
00:47:38.989 --> 00:47:41.475
<i>Everything has changed.</i>

831
00:47:44.020 --> 00:47:48.434
<i>I always prided myself on
being an outsider. but now...</i>

832
00:47:51.678 --> 00:47:55.223
<i>I feel the need to
connect with someone.</i>

833
00:47:59.929 --> 00:48:02.423
<i>I saw myself in Jeremy...</i>

834
00:48:03.159 --> 00:48:05.495
<i>But instead of helping
him like Harry helped me.</i>

835
00:48:05.559 --> 00:48:07.723
<i>I gave him a piece of
fortune-cookie advice</i>

836
00:48:07.779 --> 00:48:09.565
<i>that he never even heard.</i>

837
00:48:10.181 --> 00:48:11.764
<i>I failed him.</i>

838
00:48:12.928 --> 00:48:14.896
<i>He deserves better...</i>

839
00:48:15.820 --> 00:48:18.493
<i>And he'll get it from now on.</i>

840
00:48:41.278 --> 00:48:43.345
<i>I guess I was wrong.</i>

841
00:48:44.958 --> 00:48:47.544
<i>Jeremy did hear my advice.</i>

842
00:48:49.010 --> 00:48:51.916
<i>He killed someone
who deserved to die.</i>

843
00:48:53.810 --> 00:48:55.506
What's the status on Perry?

844
00:48:55.551 --> 00:48:57.325
I'm having him
transferred right now.

845
00:48:57.390 --> 00:48:58.963
The D.A. wants to
keep him at county.

846
00:48:58.989 --> 00:49:00.785
pending arraignment.

847
00:49:01.808 --> 00:49:03.766
Maria.

848
00:49:03.810 --> 00:49:05.395
it was your
decision making

849
00:49:05.450 --> 00:49:07.526
that led to his
capture and arrest.

850
00:49:08.741 --> 00:49:10.605
and you made all
our lives easier

851
00:49:10.651 --> 00:49:12.704
by getting the
bastard to confess.

852
00:49:12.899 --> 00:49:14.375
I'm just doing my job.

853
00:49:14.780 --> 00:49:17.574
It feels good to be
praising your police work

854
00:49:17.610 --> 00:49:19.753
instead of your
politics for a change.

855
00:49:22.310 --> 00:49:24.164
We need to make an
official comment.

856
00:49:24.211 --> 00:49:26.293
Don't worry.
I'll keep it short.

857
00:49:26.349 --> 00:49:28.713
I'm just heading downstairs
now for the press conference.

858
00:49:28.768 --> 00:49:30.506
The press conference is over.

859
00:49:31.009 --> 00:49:34.725
Oh. and. uh. don't worry.
I kept it short.

860
00:49:35.849 --> 00:49:38.105
You got to be
fucking kidding me.

861
00:49:38.161 --> 00:49:39.525
That was my bust!

862
00:49:39.570 --> 00:49:41.134
This is my department.

863
00:49:44.188 --> 00:49:46.983
Did you at least
give me credit?

864
00:49:47.210 --> 00:49:48.896
Yes.
I just gave it to you.

865
00:49:49.118 --> 00:49:51.244
Haven't you been listening?

866
00:49:58.759 --> 00:50:02.183
<i>Ever since Harry's death.
I've been alone...</i>

867
00:50:05.028 --> 00:50:06.655
<i>But now...</i>

868
00:50:06.848 --> 00:50:08.866
<i>for the first time...</i>

869
00:50:09.550 --> 00:50:11.226
<i>I feel alone.</i>

870
00:50:11.711 --> 00:50:13.823
How long you need
with the prisoner?

871
00:50:18.629 --> 00:50:20.453
As long as I can get.

872
00:50:20.651 --> 00:50:22.365
<i>Jeremy is gone.</i>

873
00:50:22.398 --> 00:50:24.214
<i>and Neil Perry
will soon vanish</i>

874
00:50:24.359 --> 00:50:26.514
<i>into the catacombs
of the system.</i>

875
00:50:27.069 --> 00:50:29.504
<i>I have so many
questions for him.</i>

876
00:50:30.579 --> 00:50:33.356
<i>How did he discover my secrets?</i>

877
00:50:33.680 --> 00:50:36.106
<i>What was his message to me?</i>

878
00:50:38.071 --> 00:50:40.164
<i>He's been in my home.</i>

879
00:50:40.308 --> 00:50:42.154
<i>my photos...</i>

880
00:50:43.010 --> 00:50:44.936
<i>my life.</i>

881
00:50:45.119 --> 00:50:46.895
<i>He knows me.</i>

882
00:50:48.049 --> 00:50:50.446
<i>Now I need to know him...</i>

883
00:50:56.590 --> 00:51:00.003
<i>...to connect face-to-face</i>

884
00:51:00.520 --> 00:51:03.666
<i>before he's beyond
my reach forever.</i>

885
00:51:15.500 --> 00:51:16.574
Hi.

886
00:51:20.001 --> 00:51:22.243
Who the fuck are you?

887
00:51:29.000 --> 00:51:34.246
Resync : ilikeit - Transcript : Raceman
